								StaticText '\ue605\ue605\ue605\ue605\ue605'

								StaticText '100%'
						StaticText "These Bambo Lane Crunchy Rice Rollers are simply delicious. They are perfect for when I want a snack that isn't high in calories, only 45 calories per roll. Each pack has 8 rollers. They are lightly sweetened with cane sugar. They have a enjoyable crunch, that can be a little messy if your not careful. I love that they are gluten free and vegan! They taste great! Packaging says its a 'Product of Korea' and they did a wonderful job creating this snack.To keep the crunchiness and freshness use a zip-lock bag, and or a chip clip."

						StaticText 'I have been enjoying Rice Rollers for sometime now. I have gotten Brown Rice Rollers and saw these, missing the fact until delivery that they are White Rice Rollers. The way they are packaged, there are eight in each wrapper. They are all stuck together though. The only way to eat them is in a broken up, crumby fashion. Not my idea of fun.'

						[2033] LayoutTable ''

								StaticText '\ue605\ue605\ue605\ue605\ue605'
								StaticText '\ue605\ue605\ue605\ue605\ue605'
								StaticText '100%'
						StaticText 'These things are insanely addictive! Dare I say delicious. Ridiculous, I know. "Delicious" and "rice cake" in the same sentence is obscured but these are no regular rice cakes. I wasn\'t too keen on the "roll" aspect since it can be tedious when spreading things like almond butter or what not on them. But unlike regular old rice cakes, I can seriously eat these by themselves. I\'m always on the run and after all the gas station/vending machine junk food started catching up with me I turned to fruit and other snacks for that mid-day energy boost. Rice cakes really have no nutritional value and most taste like cardboard when eaten alone, but pair it with some nut butter or raw honey it\'s pretty satisfying and helps with balancing my blood sugar levels throughout the day. These are way better than regular old rice cakes though. They\'re lightly sweetened with a different kind of texture that makes them (buyer beware) highly addictive.'

								StaticText '100%'
						StaticText 'These BamboonLane Crunchy Rice Rollers are just the treat for me. They come 8 rice rolls to a package, and 4 packages in total. They have a nice light, crunchy taste which satisfies any hunger pains I might have. I try not to eat snacks, but when I want one, I do not feel guilty about eating them.These rice folks are made with white ruce, cane sugar, rice syrup and agar. The rice folks are 45 calories, with no fat, no gluten, no salt, no cholesterol and are vegan. We all have the need for a crunchy something every so often, and these will fill the bill without feeling guilty or making a big dent in your calorie limit per day. They have a nice light taste, and your crunch factor will be fulfilled.Recommended. prisrob 05-01-16'
